What you need to know:

Victory in the final in Paris on June 13 will take Nadal past the record of 20 majors he currently shares with Roger FedererDespite his remarkable history in Paris, Nadal, who turns 35 on June 3, admits he remains stunned at his longevity in a sport where he has been an ever-present in the world top 10 since 2005Apart from Djokovic and Soderling, only injury has defeated Nadal in Paris when a wrist problem forced him to withdraw after the second round in 2016